 <description translatable="no">

    <p>
		EcotubeHQ is a hardware accelerated video player which requires minimal data to offer high quality video output from streaming 
		services such as YouTube, Rumble and Bitchute  	
	</p>
	<p>Features:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>EcoTubeHQ automatically downloads highest quality / lowest bitrate YouTube videos, i.e. av1 codec videos are output by default, if av1 isn't available then vp9 is utilized, and if vp9 isn't available then h.264 is output.</li>
        <li>EcoTubeHQ opens low bitrate 144p / 240p YouTube videos in reduced size windows. When these windows are ran ‘always on top’ they can be used for viewing videos which do not need full screen output [e.g. podcasts].</li>
        <li>EcoTubeHQ further minimizes data usage by restricting videos to 30fps.</li>
        <li>EcoTubeHQ offers three video upscaling techniques: AMD FidelityFX Super Resolution [Best Quality], Lanczos [High Quality] and Bicubic [Low Energy]. 720p AMD FSR video quality is comparable to conventional 1080p quality.</li>
        <li>EcoTubeHQ can minimize video artifacts through debanding.</li>
        <li>EcoTubeHQ can utilize Vulkan GPU Compute Acceleration to minimize CPU usage during video output.</li>
        <li>EcoTubeHQ offers drag and drop video playlists.</li>
        <li>EcoTubeHQ can play local video files with AMD FidelityFX Super Resolution.</li>
        <li>EcoTubeHQ offers two Opus audio bitrates for av1 and vp9 YouTube videos - 70kbps and 160kbps.</li>
      </ul>
 </description>
